                            <comment id="12627104" author="udanax" created="Fri, 29 Aug 2008 20:51:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 from me. Really needs this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12627375" author="yedingding@gmail.com" created="Mon, 1 Sep 2008 03:17:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is it better to add versions argument to the method HTable#getRow(final byte [] row, final byte [][] columns, final long ts) instead of creating this new method?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12627526" author="jimk" created="Mon, 1 Sep 2008 19:49:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good point! Made this issue a subtask of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-847&quot; title=&quot;new API: HTable.getRow with numVersion specified&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-847&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-847&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12652506" author="stack" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2008 21:03:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do&#287;acan, ok if we move this out of 0.19.0?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12652564" author="stack" created="Tue, 2 Dec 2008 22:41:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving to 0.20.0 with Do&#287;acan G&#252;ney&apos;s permission over in hbase-847&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12652934" author="stack" created="Wed, 3 Dec 2008 19:58:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do&#287;acan, can I get a famlly only with hbase-847?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12652936" author="stack" created="Wed, 3 Dec 2008 20:00:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If I do:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
getRow(row, columns, numVersions, ts)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;... where the columns are families, will this get all cells for all columns of mentioned families?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12653926" author="dogacan" created="Fri, 5 Dec 2008 21:09:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm, I haven&apos;t changed the behaviour there, so I checked and yes: passing columns will return all column families.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12653929" author="stack" created="Fri, 5 Dec 2008 21:26:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolved.  Thanks Do&#287;acan.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
